ss="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-25_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-28_">The shaping of young minds is a task entrusted to us as educators and staff of secondary schools. We bear a profound responsibility for our studentsâ€™ academic growth and physical, emotional, and psychological well-being. In the wake of this, understanding the importance of child protection and its implications within our school environment is paramount.<br><br>In this article, Anne Rodgers underscores the importance of child protection training for all school staff, emphasising its different aspects and encouraging a collective responsibility towards safeguarding our students.

<br> 
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-31_">Child protection: A legislative mandate
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Child_protection_A_legislative_mandate.png?v=1687187305" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Child_protection_A_legislative_mandate.png?v=1687187305 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Child_protection_A_legislative_mandate_500x.png?v=1687187305 320w" width="1800" height="1200" alt="Child protection: A legislative mandate - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Child protection: A legislative mandate - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-32_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-35_">In the UK, child protection is governed by numerous legislative mandates, with the Children Act 1989 &amp; 2004, the Safeguarding Vulnerable Groups Act 2006, and the Keeping Children Safe in Education 2021 being central to its edifice. However, the essence of these mandates does not merely lie in their existence; it is in their conscientious execution that we truly safeguard our students.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-36_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-38_">Child protection training
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Child_protection_training.jpg?v=1687187613" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Child_protection_training.jpg?v=1687187613 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Child_protection_training_500x.jpg?v=1687187613 320w" width="1411" height="941" alt="Child protection training - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Child protection training - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-39_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-42_">We have recently launched a comprehensive eLearning course on child protection, covering all aspects to enable us to create a safe and supportive environment for our students. The course consists of five crucial modules, including recognising possible abuse, responding appropriately, reporting concerns, recording observations and preventing abuse.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-45_">Module 1 - Recognising possible abuse


</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_1_-_Recognising_possible_abuse.jpg?v=1687187809" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_1_-_Recognising_possible_abuse.jpg?v=1687187809 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_1_-_Recognising_possible_abuse_500x.jpg?v=1687187809 320w" width="1385" height="923" alt="Module 1 - Recognising possible abuse - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Module 1 - Recognising possible abuse - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-46_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-47_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-49_">The first step to protection is recognition. Understanding the various forms of abuse, including emotional, physical, sexual, and neglect, and recognising their potential signs are the cornerstone of effective child protection.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-50_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-52_">Module 2 - Responding appropriately



</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_2_-_Responding_appropriately.jpg?v=1687188060" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_2_-_Responding_appropriately.jpg?v=1687188060 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_2_-_Responding_appropriately_500x.jpg?v=1687188060 320w" width="1981" height="1321" alt="Module 2 - Responding appropriately - Education and training - The Mandatory Trainign Group UK -" title="Module 2 - Responding appropriately - Education and training - The Mandatory Trainign Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-53_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-54_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-56_">Once we identify a potential issue, how we respond can significantly impact a child's willingness to share and seek help. This module covers the importance of non-judgmental and supportive responses to such disclosures.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-57_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-59_">Module 3 - Reporting your concerns




</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_3_-_Reporting_your_concerns.jpg?v=1687188231" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_3_-_Reporting_your_concerns.jpg?v=1687188231 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_3_-_Reporting_your_concerns_500x.jpg?v=1687188231 320w" width="1981" height="1321" alt="Module 3 - Reporting your concerns - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Module 3 - Reporting your concerns - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-60_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-61_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-63_">Reporting concerns is not just an ethical obligation; it's a legal one, too. Learn about the correct internal and, if necessary, external reporting procedures, and understand the ramifications of not reporting suspected abuse.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-64_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-66_">Module 4 - Recording your observations</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_4_-_Recording_your_observations.jpg?v=1687188347" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_4_-_Recording_your_observations.jpg?v=1687188347 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_4_-_Recording_your_observations_500x.jpg?v=1687188347 320w" width="1354" height="900" alt="Module 4 - Recording your observations - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Module 4 - Recording your observations - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-67_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-68_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-70_">The importance of accurate and factual recording can't be overstated in child protection. Learn about the type of information to record, the correct procedure for recording, and issues related to confidentiality and data protection.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-71_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-73_">Module 5 - Preventing abuse</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_5_-_Preventing_abuse.jpg?v=1687188479" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_5_-_Preventing_abuse.jpg?v=1687188479 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Module_5_-_Preventing_abuse_500x.jpg?v=1687188479 320w" width="708" height="496" alt="Module 5 - Preventing abuse - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Module 5 - Preventing abuse - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-74_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-75_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-77_">Prevention is always better than cure. This module delves into how we can create a secure environment that discourages abuse, including implementing robust anti-bullying and online safety policies.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-78_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-80_">The role of school governors in child protection</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_role_of_school_governors_in_child_protection.jpg?v=1687188582" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_role_of_school_governors_in_child_protection.jpg?v=1687188582 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_role_of_school_governors_in_child_protection_500x.jpg?v=1687188582 320w" width="1382" height="922" alt="The role of school governors in child protection - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The role of school governors in child protection - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-81_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-82_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-84_">School governors also play a critical role in setting the strategic direction for child protection. Their responsibilities include setting child protection policies, ensuring regular staff training, appointing a competent Designated Safeguarding Lead (DSL), and monitoring and evaluating our safeguarding practices.
<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-85_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-87_">Conclusion: Safeguarding our students, our future
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_Safeguarding_our_students_our_future.jpg?v=1687188678" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_Safeguarding_our_students_our_future.jpg?v=1687188678 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_Safeguarding_our_students_our_future_500x.jpg?v=1687188678 320w" width="1328" height="747" alt="Conclusion: Safeguarding our students, our future - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Conclusion: Safeguarding our students, our future - Education and training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-88_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-89_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-91_">As we look towards a future where every child feels safe and secure within our school walls, we must reflect on our role in child protection. From teachers and administrative staff to volunteers and governors, we are responsible for keeping our children safe from harm. By investing in comprehensive child protection training, we strengthen our collective capability to recognise, respond to, and prevent potential threats to our students.<br><br>Together, let's ensure our schools are more than just centres of academic learning; let's create sanctuaries where every student feels safe, valued, and heard because our collective vigilance today safeguards the well-being of our future generation.<br>
